Wall-E erred by assuming that every human was the same, all gleefully ensla=
ved by AUTO, the ship=E2=80=99s AI. In fact, though, I suspect humanity wil=
l be distributed bi-modally, with the vast majority of people happily weari=
ng their Vision Pros or watching their streaming service or viewing their T=
ikTok videos, while increasingly sovereign individuals, aided by AI, pilot =
the ship.

That may sound extreme, but again, this is why it is useful to look to medi=
a first: Brownlee =E2=80=94 one man, who started out by reviewing a media c=
enter remote on his HP laptop =E2=80=94 does in fact hold the fate of entir=
e companies and products in his hand. My bet is not that AI replaces Brownl=
ee, but that AI means Brownlee=E2=80=99s for everything, not just media.

This is probably the easiest way to understand OpenAI=E2=80=99s pricing: ye=
s there are inference costs to cover, but at the end of the day, there is a=
 disparity in how much agency people have to leverage AI; it makes perfect =
sense to segment pricing in a way that makes more money from people who hav=
e the wherewithal to derive that much more benefit.

